74.5	Samuel_Barber	Samuel Barber	Samuel Osborne Barber II (March 9, 1910 – January 23, 1981) was an American composer of orchestral, opera, choral, and piano music. His Adagio for Strings (1936) has earned a permanent place in the concert repertory of orchestras. He was twice awarded the Pulitzer Prize for music, for his opera Vanessa (1956–57) and his Concerto for Piano and Orchestra (1962). His Knoxville: Summer of 1915 (1947), a work for soprano and orchestra, sets a prose text by James Agee.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/91/Samuel_Barber.jpg/220px-Samuel_Barber.jpg
